ing Bourne在英国英格兰肯特哈特利普结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。她去世在她的家乡。"},"hr":{"1320–":"1320.–preminula","1320–1380":"1320.–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320.–preminula","1404":"1404","1320":"1320.","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339.","about 1340":"oko 1340.","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"cs":{"1320–":"1320–Zesnulá","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Zesnulá","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"okolo 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Anglie"},"da":{"1320–":"1320–Afdød","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Afdød","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"omkring 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"nl":{"1320–":"1320–Overleden","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Overleden","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"circa 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"en":{"1320–":"1320–Deceased","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Deceased","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"about 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Osborne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Osbern</i>, partly from late Old English <i>Ōsbern</i>, an Anglicized form of Old Norse <i>Ásbiǫrn</i> (from <i>áss</i> ‘god’ + <i>biǫrn</i> ‘bear’), but more usually from Norman use of the cognate ancient Germanic <i>Ōsbern</i>. <i>Osbern</i> was often treated as an alternative form of <i>Osbert</i>. For pet forms see   Hoskin   and   Opie  . The surname has also been established in Ireland (Waterford, Tipperary) since the mid 16th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Osbon","meanings":["English (Sussex): variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbourn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbourne","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Oborne","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Oborne in Dorset. The placename derives from Old English <i>wōh</i> ‘twisted, crooked’ + <i>burna</i> ‘spring, stream’.","possibly from the Middle English personal name <i>Obern</i>, an Anglo-Norman French form of <i>Osbern</i> (see   Osborne  )."]},{"name":"Orsburn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbun","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Hoskin","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Osekin</i> with prosthetic <i>H-</i>, a pet form of Anglo-Norman French names beginning with <i>Os-</i> (particularly <i>Osbert</i>, as well as <i>Osbern</i>, and <i>Osmund</i>) + the Flemish diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. All three personal names were current in medieval Cornwall or Devon; see   Osborne  ,   Osmond  , and   Opie   (a pet form of <i>Osbert</i>). Old English <i>Ōsbeorn</i>, <i>Ōsbeohrt</i>, and <i>Ōsmund</i> may also have contributed in a minor way to Middle English usage; Middle English   Oswald   is another possible source, but the name was very rare in the late 14th century. For the excrescent initial <i>H-</i>, compare   Herrick  ."]},{"name":"Osborn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Orsborn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Oborn","meanings":["English (Somerset): habitational name chiefly from Oborne in Dorset, or perhaps occasionally from Howbourne Farm in Hadlow Down, Sussex, Woburn in Bedfordshire, Woburn Park in Surrey, or Wooburn in Buckinghamshire. The placenames derive from Old English <i>wōh</i> ‘twisted, crooked’ + <i>burna</i> ‘spring, stream’, except Wooburn in Buckinghamshire, which is of uncertain etymology.","English (of Norman origin): perhaps from the Middle English personal name <i>Obern</i>, an Anglo-Norman French form of <i>Osbern</i> (see   Osborne  )."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘Morning dew’; also ‘generosity’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady John Osborne was born in 1320, in Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir John Osburn Baron of Sitting Bourne in 1339, in Hartlip, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1320–":"1320–Surnud","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1320–":"1320–Kuollut","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"noin 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"fr":{"1320–":"1320–Décédée","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Décédée","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"environ 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hartlip Swale Cliff Kent England":"Hartlip, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lady John Osborne est née en 1320, à Hartlip, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Sir John Osburn Baron of Sitting Bourne en 1339, à Hartlip, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1320–":"1320–Verstorben","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1340–1404":"1340–1404","1320–Female":"1320–Verstorben","1404":"1404","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1339":"1339","about 1340":"um 1340","Hartlip,Sittingbourne,Kent,England":"Hartlip, Kent, England, Un